This is the Perl module Attribute::TieClasses.

INSTALLATION

Attribute::TieClasses installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is
set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan Attribute::TieClasses

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Attribute::TieClasses documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Attribute::TieClasses

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

